// =============================================================================
// PODCAST PRODUCTION ENGINE :: WEBHOOKS PLUGIN ROUTE TEMPLATE (per client)
// webhook-design.md Section 2. One route per client, exactly one.
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// LIVE-VERIFIED against the INSTALLED gateway (OpenClaw 2026.6.11,
// dist/extensions/webhooks/index.js). The installed schema DIFFERS from the
// design's illustrative sketch; this template matches the installed contract, not
// the sketch (schema drift is a known trap and the design says to validate before
// shipping). Verified facts:
//
//   * Config path is  plugins.entries.webhooks.config.routes  (a MAP keyed by
//     routeId), NOT  plugins.webhooks.routes  (a list with an `id` field).
//   * Route object (.strict()): { enabled?, path?, sessionKey(req), secret(req),
//     controllerId?, description? }. `path` defaults to /plugins/webhooks/<routeId>.
//   * secret is a plain string OR a SecretRef with EXACTLY three keys
//     { source, provider, id }, source in { env, file, exec }. For source "env"
//     the runtime resolves process.env[id], so `id` is the ENV VAR NAME (must
//     match ^[A-Z][A-Z0-9_]{0,127}$) and `provider` is the "default" alias.
//   * Actions the route drives: create_flow, run_task, get_flow, find_latest_flow,
//     resolve_flow, get_task_summary, set_waiting, resume_flow, finish_flow,
//     fail_flow, request_cancel, cancel_flow. create_flow assigns the flowId (no
//     client-supplied id), so dedup is the intake ledger's exclusive-create claim
//     and the job_key rides in the flow's stateJson.
//
// Placeholders to substitute per client at onboarding (provision script):
//   <client-slug>  lowercase, dash-separated, stable for the life of the client
//                  (example: client-one, acme-media).
//
// Secret custody (NEVER a plaintext value here): generate at onboarding with
//   openssl rand -hex 32
// and place it in the client's env store as PODCAST_INTAKE_HOOK_SECRET (verify
// SET in the LIVE process environment, not just a file). The plaintext transits
// no chat, no repo, no log. Verification is "env SET" plus "signed test request
// returns 200 and unsigned returns 401", never an echo of the value. Config is
// written as the node runtime user, never root (a root-owned config freezes the
// gateway).
//
// Merge this fragment into the client's openclaw.json under plugins.entries; do
// not overwrite other plugin entries. Reload per the box's restart doctrine
// (Mac: kickstart-then-stop; Virtual Private Server: compose recreate, not bare
// restart, so env changes load), then confirm the gateway is healthy.
// =============================================================================
{
  plugins: {
    entries: {
      webhooks: {
        enabled: true,
        config: {
          routes: {
            // routeId. The slug is embedded even though the box is single-client
            // so logs are unambiguous and a copied config is detectable by the
            // post-fan-out config validator (slug vs box identity mismatch).
            "podcast-intake-<client-slug>": {
              enabled: true,
              // Origin path is fixed; the Cloudflare Tunnel forwards the public
              // hostname to this path unchanged (cloudflare-design.md owns the
              // public hostname and the POST-only WAF rule).
              path: "/plugins/webhooks/podcast-intake-<client-slug>",
              // The session owned by the client's podcast department agent. The
              // route drives TaskFlows in this session and nothing else consumes
              // it. The tool-bearing pipeline steps run in this agent's own turn
              // (sub-agents get no Model Context Protocol).
              sessionKey: "podcast:intake:<client-slug>",
              // Per-client, per-route SecretRef, re-resolved on EVERY request so a
              // rotation needs no gateway restart. source "env" resolves
              // process.env[id]; provider is the "default" alias.
              secret: {
                source: "env",
                provider: "default",
                id: "PODCAST_INTAKE_HOOK_SECRET"
              },
              // Controller id for the managed flows this route creates. The
              // controller runbook's FIRST step is the deterministic intake
              // handler (a single Bash call to scripts/webhook/intake_handler.py),
              // which maps, tenant-checks, dedup-claims, persists, and then either
              // advances to Step 1 or closes the flow for a duplicate / needs_input
              // / test / wrong-tenant delivery. No language model, no Model Context
              // Protocol in that step.
              controllerId: "webhooks/podcast-intake-<client-slug>",
              description: "Podcast Production Engine intake for <client-slug> (deterministic ingest, durable TaskFlow)."
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
